hemselves to the test, improve their language knowledge, get to know a National academic excellence and create professional relationships with the lecturers.\r\n\r\nFive different subjects are provided: Italian language and culture, writing workshop, history of art, design and Italian style, specific course in photography, video, fashion and design, a final test and a PLIDA certification.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\"%7B%22default%22%3A%7B%22padding-left%22%3A%222.5rem%22%2C%22padding-right%22%3A%222.5rem%22%7D%7D\" el_id=\"course-structure\"][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3><strong>Course Structure</strong></h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_column_text]<strong>The program envisions 476 hours of study in total, divided into 17 hours a week</strong>. The 60 credits obtained will allow students to be admitted to Ferrari Fashion School 3 year courses and Bachelor of Arts programs â or BA programs in any other Institution, keeping in mind the general rule regarding the educational and decision-making independence of all Higher Education Institutions regarding admissions â and will not be recognized for the purposes of reducing the teaching load of subsequent Degree programs.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\"%7B%22default%22%3A%7B%22padding-left%22%3A%22%22%2C%22padding-right%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%22laptops%22%3A%7B%22padding-left%22%3A%22%22%2C%22padding-right%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%22tablets%22%3A%7B%22padding-left%22%3A%222.5rem%22%2C%22padding-right%22%3A%222.5rem%22%7D%2C%22mobiles%22%3A%7B%22padding-left%22%3A%222.5rem%22%2C%22padding-right%22%3A%222.5rem%22%7D%7D\" el_id=\"study-plan\"][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3><strong>Study Plan</strong></h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_tta_accordion c_icon=\"plus\"][vc_tta_section title=\"Primo Anno\" tab_link=\"%7B%22url%22%3A%22%22%7D\" active=\"1\"][vc_column_text]I am text block. Click ed