(168, 3, '2019-12-19 14:32:01', '2019-12-19 13:32:01', 'Ferrari Fashion School Milano has recently signed a partnership with American Institute of Applied Sciences in Switzerland, for high level training in Management, Luxury and Fashion Business, in order to give its educational offer a more international direction and provide its students with the chance to access high quality academic training, recognized all over the world and valuable as a guarantee for quality and excellence.\r\n\r\nThanks to the synergy and experience gained in so many years of activity in the business, AUS and Ferrari Fashion School together designed new Bachelor and Master programs in order to train highly specialized profiles in the field of Fashion and Management.\r\n\r\nThe training paths will concern with different areas, such as Fashion Business &amp; Marketing, Fashion Design and Management, Fashion Start-up.\r\nIn the picture:\r\nÂ \r\nDr. Mohamad El KhansaÂ \r\nPresident\r\nAUS\r\nÂ \r\nMatteo Andreacchio\r\nManaging Director\r\nFerrari Fashion School Milano\r\n', 'FERRARI FASHION SCHOOL SIGNS A PARTNERSHIP WITH AMERICAN INSTITUTE OF APPLIED SCIENCES IN SWITZERLAND', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ferrari-fashion-school-signs-a-partnership-with-aus-american-university-switzerland', '', '', '2023-06-07 10:07:13', '2023-06-07 08:07:13', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=3069', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(169, 3, '2023-10-10 17:44:03', '2023-10-10 15:44:03', '\r\nFor today\'s fashion dreamers\r\nMilan, September 15, 2023 - Ferrari Fashion School announces a significant change: after 20 years of excellence in Higher Education in the Fashion and Luxury sector, the institute is changing its visual identity and expanding its scope to welcome international students.\r\n\r\nAs part of the renewal process, Ferrari Fashion School introduces a new logo that reflects its dynamism and attention to fashion trends. The red color and the initials used as a monogram emphasize the school\'s distinctive identity. Accompanying the logo is a new slogan that mirrors the characteristics of education received at Ferrari Fashion School: \'For today\'s fashion dreamers.\'\r\n\r\nA prosperous year for Ferrari Fashion School, which, in addition to revising its visual identity, becomes part of the Plena Education Group, the third-largest private group in Italy in the field of education. This partnership offers new opportunities for growth and development, positioning the school as a true boutique for Higher Fashion Education. Alongside this, there\'s a strategic partnership with Teesside University, a prestigious English university. This collaboration will promote the exchange of knowledge and skills, expanding study and research opportunities for students.\r\n\r\nFerrari Fashion School\'s main objective remains the training of \'Made in Italy\' professionals in the fashion world. Its study method, based on know-how, interdisciplinarity, and collaboration with industry companies, will continue to be central to the educational process. The school remains committed to offering students a complete immersion in the world of fashion, preparing them for the challenges of an increasingly globalized industry.', 'Ferrari Fashion School: A new chapter for Fashion.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ferrari-fashion-school-un-nuovo-capitolo-per-la-moda', '', '', '2023-11-27 10:12:13', '2023-11-27 09:12:13', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9003', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(170, 12, '2024-12-18 16:28:05', '2024-12-18 15:28:05', '\r\nFerrari Fashion School and WeRoad: A Partnership Dedicated to Adventure\r\nThe Plena Education Group, which includes Ferrari Fashion School, has signed an agreement with WeRoad, the leading tour operator specializing in group travel worldwide. This collaboration opens the door to new travel opportunities for the community of all six schools within the Plena Group.\r\n\r\nThanks to this partnership, valid from today through the end of 2025, the entire Ferrari Fashion School community can access WeRoad and WeRoad Collection trips at discounted rates, using exclusive promo codes.\r\nWhat is WeRoad?\r\nWeRoad is more than just a tour operatorâitâs a true community of road travelers. With an informal and adventurous style, its mission is to explore the world together, with backpacks on and a spirit of discovery. Travelers are guided by an expert coordinator who not only manages the itinerary but also fosters the sharing of stories, experiences, and cultures.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nWhat about the WeRoad Collection?\r\nAlongside its adventurous trips, WeRoad offers the WeRoad Collectionâa more exclusive and comfortable travel experience. In addition to exploring authentic and off-the-beaten-path destinations, this option includes stays in exclusive accommodations and private transfers, allowing travelers to enjoy moments of relaxation and rejuvenation. The hotels themselves become an integral part of the adventure, not just a stop along the way.', 'Ferrari Fashion School and WeRoad: a partnership dedicated to adventure', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ferrari-fashion-school-weroad-partnership', '', '', '2024-12-18 16:28:43', '2024-12-18 15:28:43', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=11431', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(171, 12, '2024-11-14 16:31:11', '2024-11-14 15:31:11', 'Ferrari Fashion School is committedÂ to building valuable partnerships with top-tier companies in the textile sector, offering students the opportunity to engage with hands-on projects that apply their skills and best prepare them for the professional world. Through collaborations with innovative companies, we promote initiatives that enable students to interact with high-quality materials, learn about new technologies, and understand the importance of sustainability in fashion design.\r\n\r\nThese projects represent a valuable opportunity for young designers, allowing them to express their creativity and test their skills in real briefs, thanks to the support of qualified partners.\r\n\r\nThe academic project \"Urban and Biotic\" was born in collaboration with Manteco, a leading company in the textile sector. The project will involve second-year students of the BA in Fashion Design, who will have the opportunity to develop and construct a complete outfit inspired by the men\'s FW 26 collection. Students will go through the entire creative process, working on concepts and designs that reflect both their vision and Mantecoâs values.\r\n\r\nWho is Manteco?\r\nManteco is a Tuscan company specialized in the production of carded, regenerated, and virgin wool fabrics, with a history dating back to 1941 when Enzo Anacleto founded the company. Characterized by a strong connection to tradition and a deep commitment to sustainability, Manteco is guided by a circular economy philosophy and a scientific approach to material innovation.\r\nThe project in collab with Manteco\r\nThe âUrbano e Bioticoâ project, launched in collaboration with Manteco invites students to explore the relationship between modern humans and the environment through the use of wool as a central material. Wool, a symbol of versatility and sustainability, represents a meeting point between the artificial world and the need for authenticity and well-being. Students are encouraged to reflect on the contrast between contemporary urban life and the desire for reconnection with nature, demonstrating how woolâwith its thermoregulatory properties and adaptability to both urban and natural contextsâcan meet the needs of modern humans.\r\n\r\nThe project drives them to explore the diverse textures and qualities of woolâfrom smooth, lightweight surfaces to rough, voluminous onesâto create garments that combine functionality, innovation, and a unique sensory experience. Through this experimentation, designers are encouraged to develop solutions that merge technology and craftsmanship, redefining urban wear with an eco-conscious and mindful approach.\r\nProject Details\r\nThe second-year students of the BA in Fashion Design are tasked with developing and creating a complete outfit for the FW26 men\'s collection, to be presented to Manteco. The goal is to position the pieces in the medium-high or high-end market, exploring an aesthetic that bridges the urban and formal worlds. The primary material will be wool, used in various weights and combinations to create creative solutions based on an in-depth study of volume, textile manipulation, and a selected color mix.', '\"Urban and Biotic\" the new collaboration between Ferrari Fashion School  and Manteco', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ferrari-fashion-school-with-manteco-in-the-collaboration-urban-and-biotic', '', '', '2025-06-05 18:13:25', '2025-06-05 16:13:25', '', 104, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=11296', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(172, 12, '2025-01-13 12:15:42', '2025-01-13 11:15:42', '\r\nFerrari Fashion School e WeRoad: una partnership allâinsegna dellâavventura\r\nIl Gruppo Plena Education , a cui Ferrari Fashion School appartiene, ha siglato una convenzione con WeRoad, il Tour Operator leader nellâorganizzazione di viaggi di gruppo in tutto il mondo. Questa collaborazione apre le porte a nuove opportunitÃ  di viaggio per la community delle sei scuole del gruppo Plena.\r\n\r\nGrazie a questo accordo, valido da oggi e per tutto il 2025, tutta la community Ferrari Fashion School potrÃ  accedere ai viaggi WeRoad e WeRoad Collection a tariffe agevolate, attraverso dei codici sconto dedicati.\r\nCosâÃ¨ WeRoad?\r\nWeRoad non Ã¨ solo un tour operator, ma una vera e propria community di viaggiatori on the road. Con uno stile informale e avventuroso, lâobiettivo Ã¨ scoprire il mondo in compagnia, con zaino in spalla e spirito di scoperta. I viaggiatori sono accompagnati da un coordinatore esperto che non solo gestisce lâitinerario, ma favorisce la condivisione di storie, esperienze e culture.\r\nE la WeRoad Collection?\r\nAccanto ai viaggi avventurosi, WeRoad propone la WeRoad Collection, una versione piÃ¹ esclusiva e confortevole dellâesperienza di viaggio. Oltre alla scoperta di luoghi autentici e poco turistici, questa formula prevede il soggiorno in strutture esclusive e il comfort di trasferimenti privati, permettendo ai viaggiatori di godere di momenti di relax e rigenerazione. Gli hotel diventano cosÃ¬ una parte integrante dellâavventura, non piÃ¹ solo un luogo di passaggio.', 'Ferrari Fashion School x WeRoad | Tariffe agevolate per la community', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ferrari-fashion-school-x-weroad-tariffe-agevolate-per-la-community', '', '', '2025-01-13 12:15:42', '2025-01-13 11:15:42', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=11432', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(173, 3, '2022-10-26 14:44:48', '2022-10-26 12:44:48', 'Dalla Milano Fashion Week allaÂ FESTA DEL CINEMA DI ROMASUL RED CARPET LA SFILATA DEGLI ABITI HAUTE COUTURE ISPIRATI ALLE ICONICHE FATE, REALIZZATI DAGLI STUDENTI DI FERRARI FASHION SCHOOLÂ PER FESTEGGIARE I 18 ANNI DI WINX CLUBLâalta moda incontra il mondo della magia grazie alle Winx: dopo la Milano Fashion Week, il 20 ottobre le fate piÃ¹ famose del piccolo schermo, fiore allâocchiello del Made in Italy in tutto il mondo, sono atterrate sul red carpet dellâattesissima Festa del Cinema di Roma, questâanno alla sua 17Â° edizione. Per la prima volta hanno sfilato i sei abiti haute couture ispirati ad ogni singola Winx, creati grazie alla straordinaria collaborazione che ha visto protagonisti, per la speciale occasione dei 18 anni di Winx Club, gli studenti di Ferrari Fashion School, supportati dalle giovani stiliste gemelle del brand Feleppa, Francesca e Veronica Feleppa.Â \r\n\r\nAd accompagnare i preziosi outfit sul red carpet della Festa del Cinema il âpapÃ â delle Winx in persona, Iginio Straffi: âSono davvero entusiasta di festeggiare i primi 18 anni delle mie fate con tante iniziative straordinarie come questa, e con un pubblico cosÃ¬ affiatato e variegato, che ha dimostrato anno dopo anno la capacitÃ  del brand di abbattere ogni barriera e farsi portavoce dei sogni di molti. Le Winx sono riuscite a volare cosÃ¬ lontano grazie a una community di fan globale, appassionata e fidelizzata, alla quale siamo immensamente grati e a cui dedicheremo tante belle novitÃ  in arrivo.â\r\n\r\nGli studenti vincitori si sono distinti all\'interno del percorso formativo riuscendo a cogliere appieno l\'anima e la personalitÃ  delle Winx e traducendole in outfit davvero magici. Vittorio Alessi e Miriam Pellegrin sono gli stilisti che hanno creato gli outfit di Tecna, Musa e Bloom. Valentina Lacatena, Marika Caramia e Rosalba Andolfi sono le creatrici dello stile di Aisha, mentre Stella e Flora sono state cre