(214, 8, '2023-07-12 17:59:35', '2023-07-12 15:59:35', '\r\nPREMIO SARTORIA A. CARACENI\r\nDurante il Fashion Show, in una serata all\'insegna della moda e dell\'innovazione, la Sartoria A.Caraceni ha conferito un prestigioso premio ad una giovane e talentuosa studentessa della Ferrari Fashion School. L\'evento, che ha richiamato stilisti, esperti del settore e appassionati di moda, Ã¨ stato l\'occasione perfetta per celebrare il successo e l\'innovazione dei nostri studenti nell\'industria della moda.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLa sartoria Caraceni viene fondata da Augusto Caraceni, un sarto italiano nato nel 1893. Insieme ai suoi fratelli, apprende l\'arte sartoriale dal padre e diventa famoso a Parigi negli anni \'30. Apre una sartoria a Milano nel 1946 che ancora oggi veste i personaggi dellâAlta Moda. La sartoria si distingue per l\'uso di tessuti di alta qualitÃ  e materiali naturali, per la sua maestria nell\'arte della creazione sartoriale su misura. La Sartoria ha assegnato il premio a Valentina Lacatena, una giovane promessa della moda che ha dimostrato un talento eccezionale nel campo del Fashion Design. Il premio ricevuto consiste in una targa celebrativa in argento, una forbice serigrafata e, ultimo ma non meno importante, un viaggio a Parigi per due persone.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRingraziamo la sartoria per averci omaggiato di questo premio e della loro presenza durante AQUA, Fashion Show &amp; Exhibition; porteremo avanti sicuramente nel tempo questa stretta collaborazione.', 'Premio Sartoria A. Caraceni', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'premio-caraceni', '', '', '2023-08-21 17:18:03', '2023-08-21 15:18:03', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=8322', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(215, 3, '2023-08-22 17:51:07', '2023-08-22 15:51:07', '\r\nSARTORIA A. CARACENIÂ AWARD\r\nDuring the Fashion Show, in an evening dedicated to fashion and innovation, Sartoria A.Caraceni awarded a prestigious prize to a young and talented student from Ferrari Fashion School. The event, which brought together designers, industry experts, and fashion enthusiasts, was the perfect opportunity to celebrate the success and innovation of our students in the fashion industry.\r\n\r\nThe Caraceni tailoring house was founded by Augusto Caraceni, an Italian tailor born in 1893. Together with his brothers, he learned the art of tailoring from their father and gained fame in Paris in the \'30s. He opened a tailoring house in Milan in 1946, which still dresses high-profile figures in the world of high fashion. The tailoring house stands out for its use of high-quality fabrics and natural materials, showcasing expertise in the art of bespoke tailoring. The Sartoria presented the award to Valentina Lacatena, a young fashion promise who has shown exceptional talent in the field of Fashion Design. The prize included a commemorative silver plaque, an engraved pair of scissors, and, last but not least, a trip to Paris for two.\r\n\r\nWe thank the tailoring house for honoring us with this award and for their presence during AQUA, Fashion Show &amp; Exhibition; we will surely continue this close collaboration in the future.', 'Sartoria A. Caraceni Award', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'premio-sartoria-a-caraceni', '', '', '2023-11-27 10:11:25', '2023-11-27 09:11:25', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9016', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(216, 12, '2024-11-14 16:03:06', '2024-11-14 15:03:06', 'Ferrari Fashion School si impegna a costruire collaborazioni di valore con aziende dâeccellenza del settore tessile, offrendo agli studenti lâopportunitÃ  di misurarsi con progetti concreti che mettono in pratica le loro abilitÃ  e li preparano al meglio per il mondo del lavoro. Attraverso collaborazioni con aziende innovative, promuoviamo iniziative che permettono agli studenti di interagire con materiali di alta qualitÃ , conoscere nuove tecnologie e comprendere l\'importanza della sostenibilitÃ  nel design di moda.\r\n\r\nQuesti progetti rappresentano unâoccasione preziosa per i giovani designer, che possono esprimere la propria creativitÃ  e testare le proprie capacitÃ  in brief reali grazie al supporto di partner qualificati.\r\n\r\nIn questo spirito Ã¨ nato il progetto accademico âUrbano e Bioticoâ in collaborazione con Manteco, azienda leader nel settore tessile che vedrÃ  la partecipazione della classe del secondo anno del BA in Fashion Design che avrÃ  la possibilitÃ  diÂ sviluppare e confezionare un outfit completo ispirato alla collezione uomo FW 26. Gli studenti affronteranno lâintero processo creativo, lavorando su concept e disegni che esprimeranno sia la loro visione che i valori di Manteco.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nChi Ã¨ Manteco?\r\nManteco Ã¨ un\'azienda toscana specializzata nella produzione di tessuti in lana cardata, rigenerata e vergine, con una storia che affonda le sue radici nel 1941, anno in cui Enzo Anacleto fondÃ² la compagnia. Caratterizzata da un forte legame con la tradizione e una profonda attenzione alla sostenibilitÃ , Manteco Ã¨ guidata da una filosofia di economia circolare e un approccio scientifico all\'innovazione dei materiali.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nIl progetto in collab con Manteco\r\nâUrbano e Bioticoâ lanciato insieme a Manteco invita gli studenti a esplorare la relazione tra lâuomo moderno e lâambiente attraverso lâuso della lana come materiale centrale. La lana, simbolo di versatilitÃ  e sostenibilitÃ , rappresenta un punto dâincontro tra il mondo artificiale e il bisogno di autenticitÃ  e benessere. Gli studenti devono riflettere sul contrasto tra la vita urbana contemporanea e il desiderio di riconnessione con la natura, dimostrando come la lana, con le sue proprietÃ  termoregolatrici e la sua capacitÃ  di adattarsi a contesti urbani e naturali, possa rispondere alle esigenze dellâuomo moderno.\r\n\r\nIl progetto li spinge a esplorare le diverse texture e caratteristiche della lana â da superfici lisce e leggere a quelle ruvide e voluminose â per creare capi che combinino funzionalitÃ , innovazione e un\'esperienza sensoriale unica. Attraverso questa sperimentazione, i designer sono incoraggiati a sviluppare soluzioni che uniscano tecnologia e artigianalitÃ , ridefinendo l\'abbigliamento urbano con un approccio ecologico e consapevole.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nDettagli del progetto\r\nLa classe del secondo anno del BA in Fashion Design Ã¨ chiamata a sviluppare e confezionare un outfit completo per la collezione uomo FW26, da presentare allâazienda Manteco. La collezione ha l\'obiettivo di posizionare i capi in una fascia medio-alta o alta del mercato e di esplorare unâestetica che si muove tra lâurbano e il formale. Il materiale principale sarÃ  la lana, impiegata in vari pesi e combinazioni per dare vita a soluzioni creative basate su un ampio studio dei volumi, manipolazioni tessili e un mix di colori selezionati.', 'Ferrari Fashion School con Manteco con la collab \"Urbano e Biotico\"', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'progetto-urbano-e-biotico-collaborazione-manteco', '', '', '2024-11-14 16:56:25', '2024-11-14 15:56:25', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=11295', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(217, 3, '2021-06-28 16:48:37', '2021-06-28 14:48:37', 'PUBBLICAZIONI FASHION MAGAZINESI nostri studenti del Master in Fashion Photography in collaborazione con il 2Â° anno del corso in Fashion Styling &amp; Digital Communication sono stati selezionati per la pubblicazione dei loro scatti da alcuni magazine d\'importanza internazionale nel settore tra cui: Imirage Magazine, Scorpio Jin Magazine, Hunter Magazine, Boyfriend Magazine, Horizon Magazine e Selin Magazine.\r\n\r\nIn arrivo nelle prossime settimane le nuove pubblicazioni.', 'PUBBLICAZIONI FASHION MAGAZINES', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pubblicazioni-fashion-magazines', '', '', '2021-06-28 18:09:23', '2021-06-28 16:09:23', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=4814', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(218, 8, '2023-09-15 13:03:41', '2023-09-15 11:03:41', '\r\nPer chi sogna un Presente nella Moda\r\nMilano, 15 settembre 2023 - Ferrari Fashion School annuncia un importante cambiamento: da 20 anni eccellenza nell\'Alta Formazione nel settore della Moda e del Lusso, l\'istituto cambia la sua identitÃ  visiva e amplia il suo raggio d\'azione per accogliere studenti internazionali.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCome parte del processo di rinnovamento, Ferrari Fashion School presenta un nuovo logo che riflette la sua dinamicitÃ  e l\'attenzione ai trend della moda. Il colore rosso e le iniziali utilizzate come monogramma sottolineano l\'identitÃ  distintiva della scuola. Al logo si affianca un nuovo claim, che rispecchia le caratteristiche di una formazione ricevuta in Ferrari Fashion School: âPer chi sogna un Presente nella Modaâ.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUn anno florido per Ferrari Fashion School, che oltre a rivedere sua identitÃ  visiva, entra a far parte del Gruppo Plena Education, il terzo gruppo privato italiano nel campo della formazione. Questa partnership offre nuove opportunitÃ  di crescita e sviluppo, posizionando la scuola come una vera boutique dell\'Alta Formazione della moda. A ciÃ² si affianca la partnership strategica con Teesside University, prestigiosa universitÃ  inglese. Questa collaborazione promuoverÃ  lo scambio di conoscenze e competenze, ampliando le opportunitÃ  di studio e ricerca per gli studenti.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nL\'obiettivo principale di Ferrari Fashion School rimane la formazione di professionisti del \"Made in Italy\" nel mondo della moda. Il suo metodo di studio, basato sul saper fare, l\'interdisciplinaritÃ  e la collaborazione con aziende del settore, continuerÃ  ad essere centrale nel processo educativo. La scuola rimane impegnata a offrire agli studenti un\'immersione completa nel mondo della moda, preparandoli per le sfide di un settore sempre piÃ¹ globalizzato.', 'Ferrari Fashion School: Un nuovo capitolo per la Moda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rebranding', '', '', '2023-09-15 13:25:26', '2023-09-15 11:25:26', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=8544', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(219, 8, '2023-09-15 13:19:06', '2023-09-15 11:19:06', '\r\n\r\n\r\nMilan, September 15th, 2023 - Ferrari Fashion School announces a significant change: after 20 years of excellence in Higher Education in the Fashion and Luxury sector, the institution is changing its visual identity and expanding its scope to welcome international students.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAs part of the renewal process, Ferrari Fashion School unveils a new logo that reflects its dynamism and attention to fashion trends. The red and initials used as a monogram emphasize the school\'s distinctive identity. Accompanying the logo is a new slogan that mirrors the characteristics of education received at Ferrari Fashion School: \"For Todays Fashion Dreamers.\"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA flourishing year for Ferrari Fashion School, which, in addition to revising its visual identity, has become part of the Plena Education Group, the third-largest private education group in Italy. This partnership offers new growth and development opportunities, positioning the school as a true boutique of High Fashion Education. Alongside this, there is a strategic partnership with Teesside University, a prestigious English university. This collaboration will promote the exchange of knowledge and skills, expanding study and research opportunities for students.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFerrari Fashion School\'s primary goal remains the training of professionals in the \"Made in Italy\" fashion world. Its method of study, based on hands-on experience, interdisciplinarity, and collaboration with industry companies, will continue to be central to the educational process. The school remains committed to providing students with a comprehensive immersion in the world of fashion, preparing them for the challenges of an increasingly globalized industry.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Ferrari Fashion School: New Fashion Era', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rebranding', '', '', '2023-09-15 13:33:31', '2023-09-15 11:33:31', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=8558', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(220, 3, '2023-06-22 18:04:39', '2023-06-22 16:04:39', '\r\nResponsible Fashion: Commitment to a Sustainable Future\r\nFashion is an ever-evolving industry, but in recent years, it has faced a significant challenge: moving beyond fast fashion. This model of rapid production and consumption has dominated the industry for years, but an increasing number of consumers and industry stakeholders are seeking more sustainable alternatives. In this article, we will explore whether the fashion market is ready to move past fast fashion and embrace a more sustainable future.\r\n\r\nIn recent years, fast fashion has faced mounting criticism for its negative environmental impacts and its effects on industry workers. The fashion industry has become one of the most polluting worldwide, with excessive production generating vast amounts of waste and irresponsible consumption often leading to garments quickly deteriorating after minimal use. Additionally, many fast fashion companies have been embroiled in scandals related to labor exploitation, shedding light on precarious working conditions along the supply chain.\r\n\r\nFortunately, consumers are becoming increasingly aware of the impact of their clothing choices. Today, many people are seeking brands that are transparent about their production practices and offer sustainable alternatives. The demand for ethical and sustainable fashion is steadily growing, compelling companies to reconsider their business models and invest in more sustainable practices.\r\n\r\nSome companies are emerging as examples of a different approach to fashion. Ethical and sustainable fashion brands are gaining popularity by offering garments made from eco-friendly materials, utilizing low-impact production processes, and ensuring ethical working conditions throughout the supply chain. Additionally, the concept of circular fashion is gaining traction, promoting reuse, recycling, and rethinking ownership, pushing towards a fashion model based on renting and swapping.\r\n\r\nIn addition to changes at the consumer and corporate levels, institutions and industry players are taking steps to promote more sustainable fashion. Governmental bodies are introducing regulations aimed at reducing the industry\'s environmental impact, promoting transparency in the supply chain, and incentivizing sustainable production practices. Simultaneously, many fashion schools are integrating sustainability education into their curricula, preparing the next generation of designers to be mindful of the challenges and opportunities related to sustainable fashion.\r\n\r\nWhile fast fashion has dominated the fashion industry for years, the market appears to be finally ready to move beyond it. Consumers are increasingly aware of production and consumption-related issues and are seeking more sustainable alternatives. Companies are responding to this demand by adopting more ethical and sustainable business models. Institutions and industry players are doing their part in promoting more responsible fashion and integrating sustainability into educational programs. The future of fashion seems to be heading towards greater sustainability, offering opportunities for a fairer, environmentally conscious, and socially responsible industry.', 'Responsible Fashion: Commitment to a Sustainable Future', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'responsible-fashion-commitment-to-a-sustainable-future', '', '', '2023-11-27 10:10:30', '2023-11-27 09:10:30', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9030', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(221, 12, '2024-03-14 17:08:40', '2024-03-14 16:08:40', 'Ferrari Fashion School: a message of hope and rebirth through fashion with #RestartCollection\r\nFerrari Fashion School, in collaboration with Terre des Hommes, unveiled a collection during Milano Fashion WeekÂ  that transcends the traditional concept of fashion, becoming a symbol of rebirth for women and girls who have endured abuse.\r\nFrom an idea by the creative agency ACNE, #RestartCollection is part of the \'InDifesa\' project and Milano \'CittÃ  delle Donne\' movement dedicated to themes of female empowerment, combating violence, and gender discrimination.\"\r\nThe Creative Process\r\nDuring the creative workshop, fashion and textile design students, through a sartorial approach transformed ripped and damaged garments that symbolizing episodes of violence into unique pieces that can tell stories of rebirth, using a tailoring approach.\r\n\"The garments were created [...], drawing inspiration from the technique of Kintsugi, the Japanese art of repairing broken objects with gold,\" explained Anna Lottersberger, Director of Ferrari Fashion School - Plena Education Group. \"Each piece thus becomes a symbol of renewal, an icon to be worn with strength and pride to convey a simple yet fundamental message: every wound can be healed, every story can begin again.\"\r\nThe young fashion designers involved in the project worked with passion and dedication under the guidance of Giusy Liguori, Course Leader of the Fashion Design course, and instructor Eva Rondinelli, demonstrating through their creations that every story can have a new beginning.\r\nCollection Launch\r\nThe launch event of the collection saw the participation of key figures in addressing these issues, such as Stefania Bartoccetti, founder of Telefono Donna, Paolo Ferrara, General Director of Terre des Hommes Italy and Daniela Simonetti, journalist and founder of ChangeTheGame, spoke about restarting after the trauma of abuse, about hope, and inner strength.\r\n\"In Italy, over 12 million girls and women have experienced violence. Of these, only 26,000 have turned to organizations or institutions for support in facing the trauma,\" Paolo Ferrara recounted during the talk. \"We know how today our society still blames victims instead of demanding a cultural change that defeats the discrimination and stereotypes that fuel gender violence. Those who experience violence cannot be abandoned and stigmatized but need all the support and care necessary to face such a heavy trauma and start anew. The Restart Collection helps us convey this message of hope in an innovative way and, thanks to the creativity of the students at Ferrari Fashion School, has allowed us to reach the new generations, the true agents of change.\"\r\nThe project allowed young designers from Ferrari Fashion School to test themselves as designers in interpreting current and highly significant issues, leading them to embrace the mission that fashion should have in contemporary society.', 'A message of hope and rebirth through fashion with #RestartCollection', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'restart-fashion-show-fabbrica-del-vapore-milan', '', '', '2025-05-31 18:13:38', '2025-05-31 16:13:38', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9965', 0, 'news', '', 0),
