(229, 3, '2023-04-23 10:32:23', '2023-04-23 08:32:23', '\r\nTalent in Store\r\nFrom April 17th to 23rd, Milan hosts the Salone del Mobile and Fuorisalone, and on this occasion, Ferrari Fashion School launches the second edition of the \'Talent in Store\' project at its headquarters, Via Enrico Pestalozzi, 4.\r\n\r\n\'Talent in Store\' offers the school\'s alumni the opportunity to exhibit and sell their collection\'s products at the heart of the Tortona Design District in Milan, all for free. It\'s a unique chance to present themselves to the publicâan experience that only Ferrari Fashion School provides to its former studentsâto support the careers of those who decide to launch their own brand.\r\n\r\nSilvia Ferrari, the Academy\'s director, expressed, \'Given the success of the last edition in 2022, we wanted to once again give our students the opportunity to showcase their talent within the prestigious international context of Fuorisalone. We hope that Talent in Store becomes increasingly a reference point for the public, companies, and industry professionals, a platform to discover emerging young creatives capable of responding professionally, creatively, and innovatively to the needs of an ever-evolving global market.\'\r\n\r\nIt\'s a moment of connection and cross-pollination between fashion, design, and the city of Milan, showcasing the evolution of contemporary fashion through the eyes of young emerging designers.\r\n\r\nTalent in Store will take place from April 21st to 22nd, featuring:\r\n\r\n 	Amelia Pandini: Brand: \'Who Am I project\' Collection: Women\'s bags\r\n 	Federica Ghirardi: Brand: \'Uma Milano\' Collection: Women\'s bags and accessories\r\n 	Filippo Regnani: Brand: \'GNINT\' Collection: Women\'s capsule and accessories\r\n 	Ilaria Scanavini: Brand: \'Breathe studio\' Collection: Women\'s capsule and accessories\r\n 	Bianca Tosa: Brand: \'t0____31\' Collection: Women\'s capsule\r\n\r\nWe look forward to seeing you at Via Enrico Pestalozzi 4