(230, 3, '2022-11-23 10:47:21', '2022-11-23 09:47:21', '\r\nTALK ABOUT FASHION SEASONS\r\nThe fashion seasons are periods during which new clothing, accessories, and footwear collections for the following year are presented. There are four fashion seasons:\r\n\r\n 	Autumn/Winter: between February and March, ahead of the autumn season. Designers showcase their warmer and darker creations like coats, jackets, sweaters, and heavy trousers. The color palette usually includes warm tones like brown, red, and gold.\r\n 	Spring/Summer: between September and October, ahead of the spring season. Designers present their lighter and colorful creations such as light dresses, skirts, tops, and lightweight trousers. The color palette typically includes cool tones like green, blue, and pastel pinks.\r\n 	Pre-Fall: between December and January, ahead of the autumn season. Designers showcase intermediate creations between Autumn/Winter and Spring/Summer, like wool jackets, sweaters, and dresses.\r\n 	Cruise: between November and December, ahead of the summer season. Designers present their holiday creations, including light dresses, swimwear, and summer accessories.\r\n\r\nFashion seasons are significant events in the fashion world that set trends and styles for the following year. These events are closely followed by industry professionals, buyers, stylists, and fashion enthusiasts.', 'Talk about Fashion Seasons', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'talk-about-fashion-seasons', '', '', '2023-11-27 10:09:12', '2023-11-27 09:09:12', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9049', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(231, 8, '2023-07-07 16:00:05', '2023-07-07 14:00:05', '\r\nTeesside University: Educational Partner\r\nAd una settimana da AQUA: Fashion Show &amp; Exhibition, Ferrari Fashion School presenta la Teesside UniversityÂ come Educational Partner ufficiale.\r\n\r\nDue studenti della rinomata universitÃ  Inglese hanno partecipato al Fashion Show AQUA, facendo sfilare i propri capi realizzati per lâoccasione. Di seguito unâintervista esclusiva ad Harry Tribe, studente di Fashion Design presso la Teesside University che racconta la sua esperienza e il percorso che lo ha portato a sfilare a Milano.\r\n\r\nQuella con Teesside Ã¨ una partnership che coltiveremo: Ferrari Fashion School Ã¨ aperta allâinnovazione e lâinternazionalizzazione per preparare gli studenti ad affrontare le sfide e a cogliere le opportunitÃ  in un mondo sempre piÃ¹ globalizzato. Favoriremo lo scambio di conoscenze e competenze, ampliando le opportunitÃ  di studio e ricerca, promuovendo la mobilitÃ  studentesca, incoraggiando la collaborazione nella ricerca e contribuendo al raggiungimento di obiettivi comuni. Questa collaborazione migliorerÃ  sicuramente la qualitÃ  dell\'istruzione, stimolando l\'innovazione e favorendo il progresso scientifico.', 'Teesside University: Educational Partner', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'teesside', '', '', '2023-08-21 17:39:48', '2023-08-21 15:39:48', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=8300', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(232, 3, '2023-07-22 17:52:35', '2023-07-22 15:52:35', '\r\nTeesside University: Educational Partner\r\nA week before AQUA: Fashion Show &amp; Exhibition, Ferrari Fashion School introduces Teesside University as its official Educational Partner.\r\n\r\nTwo students from the renowned English university participated in the AQUA Fashion Show, showcasing their creations specifically designed for the occasion. Below is an exclusive interview with Harry Tribe, a Fashion Design student at Teesside University, sharing his experience and the journey that led him to walk the runway in Milan.\r\n\r\nThe partnership with Teesside is one we aim to nurture: Ferrari Fashion School is open to innovation and internationalization to prepare students for challenges and opportunities in an increasingly globalized world. We\'ll facilitate the exchange of knowledge and skills, expand study and research opportunities, promote student mobility, encourage collaborative research, and contribute to achieving common goals. This collaboration will undoubtedly enhance the quality of education, fostering innovation and contributing to scientific progress.', 'Teesside University: Educational Partner', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'teesside-university-educational-partner', '', '', '2023-11-27 10:11:16', '2023-11-27 09:11:16', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9018', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(233, 3, '2023-05-23 10:27:57', '2023-05-23 08:27:57', '\r\nThe Cruise shows return around the world from Chanel to Louis Vuitton.\r\nCruise shows originated to initially cater to the fashion needs of the wealthiest clients who traveled to exotic locations or went on cruises during winter. Today, they aim to capture the attention of top international clients with bespoke novelties between one collection and another. Also known as Pre-Fall, they indeed preview the main lines. Today, Chanel will take the spotlight! The Chanel Cruise 2023 collection was previewed at the Monte-Carlo Beach Hotel last May, but it made a stop at the private beach of the Hotel Faena in Miami, enchanting the audience with its theatrical set designed by director Baz Luhrmann and costume designer Catherine Martin. The inspiration for this collection merges different worlds such as motor racing, tennis, the Monte Carlo ballet, the casino, and the Riviera, giving life to elegant and refined silhouettes. Among the standout pieces, racing pilot jumpsuits are prominent, one of the upcoming season\'s trends, presented in tweed or adorned with the Chanel logo. The runway also featured classic suits, checkered and striped prints, alongside primary colors like blue and red or classic black and white. The presence of Maison ambassadors like Pharrell Williams, Lily-Rose Depp, Marion Cotillard, Caroline de Maigret, and Phoebe Tonkin made the show even more special, along with other famous figures like actresses Ella Balinska and Arden Cho, actor AndrÃ©s Velencoso, and musician Nile Rodgers, who performed with CHIC, including a special appearance by Pharrell for a rendition of the hit \'Get Lucky\'. But what\'s Chanel\'s connection with America? Mademoiselle Gabrielle Chanel had a strong link with the country, receiving an invitation in 1931 to Hollywood, where she went with her friend Misia Sert and returned for a second time in 1954. In 1957, Coco Chanel received the prestigious Neiman Marcus Award. Furthermore, Coco was the first to reinvent the cruise look, a collection designed for beach life, which she herself adored. Years later, former creative director Karl Lagerfeld chose Miami as the destination to present the Chanel Cruise 2008-2009 collection, establishing a special relationship with the city. This intertwines American fashion and culture with French elegance and style, creating a unique and refined mix, just like the Chanel Cruise 2023 collection. Stay tuned!', 'The Cruise shows return around the world from Chanel to Louis Vuitton.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-cruise-shows-return-around-the-world-from-chanel-to-louis-vuitton', '', '', '2023-11-27 10:10:20', '2023-11-27 09:10:20', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9036', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(234, 3, '2023-02-23 10:36:37', '2023-02-23 09:36:37', '\r\nThe Environmental Impact of Fast Fashion: Exploring Sustainable Solutions\r\nThe fashion system is one of the largest and most influential sectors in the global economy, but the immense production and consumption of clothing have a significant environmental impact. The fashion industry has faced considerable criticism in recent years due to the pollution caused by clothing production and disposal, leading to a growing interest in sustainable fashion. The environmental impact of the fashion system is extensive and complex. Firstly, the industry uses large amounts of water and chemicals to produce fabrics and garments. For instance, the production of a single pair of jeans requires an average of 7,000 liters of water. Additionally, the industry often uses synthetic materials like polyester, which require petroleum and other fossil fuels for production and are not biodegradable. Secondly, the fashion system generates vast amounts of waste. On average, an individual produces about 70 kilograms of textile waste per year. Much of these clothes end up in landfills, where they can take up to 200 years to degrade. Furthermore, the production of fast and low-cost clothing has led to a culture of \"use and throw away,\" where garments are worn only a few times before being discarded. Lastly, the production of low-cost clothing often has severe consequences for industry workers. Many workers in developing countries are underpaid and forced to work in hazardous conditions. The fashion industry has begun addressing these issues through the introduction of sustainable fashion. This term refers to an approach to fashion that aims to reduce the industry\'s environmental and social impact. Sustainable fashion may involve the use of organic or recycled fabrics, adopting eco-friendly production practices, and supporting industry workers. However, sustainable fashion remains an expensive and often inaccessible option for consumers. Many people are unwilling to pay more for sustainable products, and the fashion industry has yet to find a way to make sustainable fashion more affordable and accessible to everyone. Overall, the environmental impact of the fashion system is a complex problem that requires ongoing attention. Consumers can do their part by purchasing sustainable products and considering the production practices of the companies they choose to support. However, this alone is not enough. It\'s also crucial for the fashion industry to genuinely commit to reducing its environmental and social impact and make sustainable fashion an accessible and affordable option for all.', 'The Environmental Impact of Fast Fashion: Exploring Sustainable Solutions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-environmental-impact-of-fast-fashion-exploring-sustainable-solutions', '', '', '2024-06-03 12:32:25', '2024-06-03 10:32:25', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?p=9045', 0, 'news', '', 0);
