(298, 3, '2019-12-03 12:02:35', '2019-12-03 11:02:35', '\r\nCAD 2D - PATTERN MAKER\r\n\r\nMASTER IN CAD 2D - PATTERN MAKER\r\nMaster - Milan\r\nThe course aims to prepare the student for the world of work, proposing exercises taken directly from work done in clothing companies during the course. During the course, each student will have a CAD workstation with ASSYST software. Great attention is paid to all the functions of modification and control of the models.\r\n\r\nAll the CAD themes are dealt with, from the construction of the model to the development of sizes up to the final placement on fabric.\r\n\r\nAt the end of the course and upon passing the final exam, the 2D Cad Modellist Master\'s Certificate will be issued.\r\nCourse details:\r\n\r\n 	Location: Milan\r\n 	1st Session: 7 October 2021\r\n 	2nd Session: 10 January 2021\r\n 	Normal Duration: 4 Months\r\n 	Intensive Duration: 2 Months\r\n 	Registration fee: â¬ 988\r\n 	Annual fee: â¬ 1100\r\n 	Final exam fee: â¬ 50\r\n\r\nBOOK A CUSTOM OPEN DAY\r\nRECIPIENTS\r\nTo be admitted to the Masters courses, students must be over 21 years of age and be in possession of a Diploma / Degree in Model making / Tailoring or other qualifications (or documented work experience) obtained both in Italy and abroad, recognized as suitable. The selection of students admitted to the Masters is made through a motivational interview and an admission test aimed at identifying the formal qualities and technical skills possessed by the candidate.\r\n\r\nFor those who start from scratch and do not have any knowledge of modeling, it is first necessary to attend the Modellist course (15 months) before entering the Master of Specialization Cad for 50 hours.\r\nTRAINING OBJECTIVES\r\nThe course aims to prepare the student for the world of work, proposing a study program and a teaching methodology aimed at providing an excellent ability to use Cad software specialized for the fashion sector. During the course exercises taken directly from work carried out in clothing companies. During the course, each student will have a CAD / CAM workstation with ASSYST software.\r\nPROFESSIONAL OPPORTUNITIES\r\nThe 2D Cad modeler can work as an employee at fashion companies and clothing companies that have industrial production.\r\nSTUDY PROGRAMS\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Operating system\r\n 	Registry and Codes\r\n 	Notches and holes\r\n 	Geometric shapes\r\n 	Accelerator keys\r\n 	variants\r\n 	Size Development\r\n 	Symmetry and Cut\r\n 	Changing the Bases\r\n 	Sewing margins\r\n 	Extraction\r\n 	Fusion and Creation\r\n 	Measurement and Control\r\n 	Print Templates\r\n 	Print placements\r\n 	Saving\r\n 	Clamps\r\n\r\n\r\nEXAMS AND CHECKS\r\nWe carry out quarterly verification tests, following the progress of the study plan so as to constantly monitor the student\'s performance and to be able to help him / her in the event of difficulties or delays in the study program.\r\n\r\nOnce the course program has been successfully completed, the student can enter the final exam to obtain the 2D CAD Model Maker Certificate which will allow him to enter the world of work directly as a highly qualified professional.BOOK A CUSTOM OPEN ', 'Model CAD / Cam Assyst', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cad-cam-model', '', '', '2020-10-20 16:43:12', '2020-10-20 14:43:12', '', 2974, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=2929', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(299, 3, '2019-12-03 16:32:26', '2019-12-03 15:32:26', '\r\nProfessional Course\r\nTailoring\r\n\r\nCourse Details\r\nLocation: Milan\r\n\r\nDuration: 3 academic years\r\n\r\nStart: October 2025\r\n\r\nClasses: max 10 students\r\n\r\nLanguage: Italian/English\r\nExplore craftsmanship in Made in Italy through advanced tailoring training and learn to create high-fashion garments.\r\nThis three-year course is an extraordinary opportunity for fashion and craftsmanship enthusiasts who wish to craft bespoke clothing that embodies elegance and sophistication. Learn traditional and innovative techniques that will transform your passion for fashion into a rewarding and prestigious profession.INFO REQUEST\r\nMain topics\r\n\r\nTailoring and Patternmaking\r\n\r\n\r\n 	PrÃªt-Ã -porter and haute couture tailoring\r\n 	Basic and advanced pattern making\r\n 	Traditional tailoring techniques\r\n\r\n\r\nClothes Customization\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Interpretation and development\r\n 	Customization and tailoring\r\n 	History of fashion and costume\r\n\r\n\r\nFashion Culture\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Culture of materials\r\n 	Mannequin manipulation\r\n 	Study of silhouettes and fit\r\n\r\n\r\nDiscover the Tailor profession\r\nA specialized high-fashion tailor is a luxury artisan who masters the art of creating garments of the highest quality and prestige. In the world of fashion and the textile industry, the specialized tailor is one of the most sought-after professionals for their ability to materialize the creative ideas through interpretative, manual, and extremely precise skills, combined with technical expertise related to forms, fabrics, and materials.\r\nTarget audience\r\nThe course is open to anyone with a passion for fashion and a particular interest in tailoring craftsmanship. The program is designed to adapt to the needs of each student, whether they are beginners or have previous experience in the industry, as the diversity of backgrounds will contribute to creating a rich and stimulating learning environment.\r\nEducational aim\r\nThe course aims to train highly qualified tailors capable of managing the entire process of creating high-fashion and luxury prÃªt-Ã -porter garments. Students will acquire advanced skills in fabric selection, precision cutting, and sewing mastery. Additionally, they will develop aesthetic sensitivity and learn to collaborate with creatives to translate their needs into wearable masterpieces.\r\nAdmission requirements\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Minimum age: 18 years\r\n\r\nThe Tailoring course can open doors to various career prospects, including:Create high-fashion and prÃªt-Ã -porter garments, applying traditional and innovative tailoring techniques.Collaborate with fashion designers to develop high-end collections for prestigious brands.Work directly with private clients to create a bespoke wardrobe that reflects their style and individuality.Manage and lead high-fashion ateliers, overseeing the work of a team of tailors and pattern makers.\r\nREQUEST INFORMATION\r\nFill in the form and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\r\nWould you prefer to speak directly with our Orientation Team?\r\nClick here and book a personalised interview.\r\', 'Tailoring', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sartoria-pret-a-porter', '', '', '2024-11-13 16:42:03', '2024-11-13 15:42:03', '', 2974, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=2934', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(300, 3, '2019-12-09 09:31:30', '2019-12-09 08:31:30', '\r\nInfo and Student Services\r\n\r\nCultural Activities\r\nThe Academy is committed to promoting culture through a wide range of initiatives that go beyond the traditional academic context, actively collaborating with external partners to organize cultural events that provide students with a comprehensive and enriching experience.\r\n\r\nFerrari Fashion School closely collaborates with museums and art galleries to arrange exclusive visits, allowing students to immerse themselves in the creative inspiration that only art can offer.\r\n\r\nThe Academy thus becomes the place where the ongoing dialogue between creativity and culture merges with practical learning and concrete experience, creating a student community that embraces diversity and innovation.\r\nLibrary\r\nThe Academy\'s Library is open from Monday to Friday, from 9:00 to 13:00, offering an extensive collection of both paper and digital resources, including texts, industry journals, and both Italian and international periodicals.\r\n\r\nThrough an agreement with the Milanese Library System (SBM), consisting of 24 neighborhood libraries, the central library at Palazzo Sormani, and the Bibliobus, students at Ferrari Fashion School have access to a unified catalog. The libraries, open to the public from Monday to Saturday, promote free access to knowledge and information without distinction of gender, social status, or religious creed.\r\nLibrary\r\n\r\nThe Academy\'s Library is open from Monday to Friday, from 9:00 to 13:00, offering an extensive collection of both paper and digital resources, including texts, industry journals, and both Italian and international periodicals.\r\nhrough an agreement with the Milanese Library System (SBM), consisting of 24 neighborhood libraries, the central library at Palazzo Sormani, and the Bibliobus, students at Ferrari Fashion School have access to a unified catalog. The libraries, open to the public from Monday to Saturday, promote free access to knowledge and information without distinction of gender, social status, or religious creed.\r\nScholarships\r\nFerrari Fashion School, to support and enhance the talent of deserving students, offers scholarships for the 2025/2026 academic year, aiming to promote their education in the fashion industry.DOWNLOAD HERE\r\nStudent Loan \"Per Merito\" from Intesa Sanpaolo\r\nFerrari Fashion School students can count on financial support designed by Intesa Sanpaolo to enable them to expand their skills. âPer Meritoâ is a loan that any student residing in Italy can obtain on the sole condition of being in good standing with their chosen course of study and requires no collateral. The loan will be disbursed starting in June of the first year, following the achievement of at least 20 educational credits.\r\n\r\nâBy Meritâ allows you to meet tuition fees, purchase of educational materials, housing expenses, and anything else you need to have peace of mind about your course of study. And students have no obligation to report these expenses.\r\n\r\nAt the end of the studies, a 24-month âbridge periodâ is activated, during which the student will not receive any more disbursements, but will not yet have to repay anything.\r\nRepayment takes place over a maximum period of 30 years; in case of early repayment there are no additional costs.\r\nThe rate is fixed and defined at the time of underwriting.\r\n\r\nAll interest is paid back by Intesa Sanpaolo to the Fund for Impact, the fund created for groups with difficulties in accessing credit and education.\r\nFor contract terms and conditions consult the Information Sheets available in Branches and on the bankâs website. The granting of loans is subject to the bankâs approval.\r\nPLEASE NOTE:\r\nStudents who wish to apply for the Merit Loan must possess residency in Italy.\r\nOnce the bank confirms the release of the loan, disbursements are made in semi-annual tranches and not concurrently with the Ferrari Fashion School maturities.\r\nFerrari Fashion School does not have any other arrangements with the bank other than those listed in the Merit Loan Guide.APPLY HEREDISCLAIMER\r\nAdvertising message with promotional purpose. âPer Meritoâ is a credit product dedicated to students attending Universities in Italy and abroad, or Postgraduate Training Institutions. For contract terms and conditions consult the Information Sheets available in branches and on the bankâs website. For more information ask your branch manager or go to the per Merito tab at www.intesasanpaolo.com in the youth section.\r\nCareer service\r\nThrough the Career Service, students have the opportunity to connect with companies and institutional partners, including the organization of Career Days and support in the search for companies in the industry, factories, and showrooms for both curricular and extra-curricular activities in Italy and abroad.Internship is an educational experience that a student undergoes at a facility affiliated with the Ferrari Fashion School (organization or company) to gain direct knowledge of the working world. The internship is optional and may include credit recognition (maximum 6 ECTS). The internship aims to \"create moments of alternation between study and work within the training processes and facilitate career choices through direct knowledge of the working world.\" The purposes of the internship can be diverse: orientational, primarily aiming to acquaint students with the reality of the working world through direct contact; formative, allowing to deepen, verify, and expand the learning received from the course of study. For the Academy, it is an opportunity to verify the coherence between the educational paths of the study courses and the potential occupational outcomes that students aspire to. From the company\'s perspective, the internship constitutes an advantageous opportunity to exchange with young bearers of up-to-date scientific knowledge and also an opportunity to train \"young talents\" to possibly integrate into their staff on a permanent basis.The internship does not represent an employment relationship. It should be the result of the meeting between the student\'s expressed interest in the discipline in which they intend to carry out the internship, the availability of the Tutor to identify and plan the training activity to be carried out, and the possibility of carrying out this activity in a company. The relationship between the Academy and the \"company\" is formalized through an agreement to which a Training Project must be attached.\r\n\r\nTo activate an internship, it is necessary for the facility hosting the student to have an active agreement with Ferrari Fashion School. If there is no existing agreement between the hosting facility and the Academy, it can be drawn up by completing the agreement, also at the suggestion of the students, by sending an email to the Placement Office â placement@ferrarifashionschool.com.\r\nStudent support\r\nThe Academy assists students in finding accommodation in private apartments and/or with affiliated real estate agencies. For further details, refer to the active agreements for accommodation search.Through the signing of specific agreements, the Academy offers students access to discounts at stores for artistic materials, fabrics, haberdasheries, copy shops, printing houses, gyms, bars, and restaurants, etc.Discover all the agreementsThe Academy inaugurates each academic year by organizing a welcome day for new students, during which the faculty, facilities, and staff are presented. Information is also provided regarding academic and extra-curricular activities, such as exams, internships, participation in events and fashion shows, as well as the delivery of the Welcome Pack.The Academy provides new students with a welcome kit and introductory educational materials for the course.Through the DSA support service, the Academy ensures regular use of spaces, equipment, and services, as well as the use of dispensation measures for exams to remove obstacles to the learning process. Students can contact the DSA representative, Dr. Francesca Corti, at the email address dsa.support@ferrarifashionschool.com.\r\nInternational Students\r\nSupport in completing procedures related to stay in Italy, such as visa application, residence permit, tax code, opening a bank account, translation of any documents.The Academy provides informational support to international students for obtaining a visa. It is strongly recommended to enroll at least 6 months before the course start date, as the visa issuance process by Italian consular authorities could be lengthy. For detailed information on the visa issuance procedure, you can contact the Orientation Office at the email address admission@ferrarifashionschool.com.The Academy provides support to students in enrolling in the National Health Service to facilitate procedures related to choosing a primary care physician and scheduling medical appointments.\r\nLanguage courses\r\n\r\nIn collaboration with CIELS Campus\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCIELS CampusÂ is a university-level Campus forÂ Socio-cultural Language Mediation, aiming to train professionals with a solid background in foreign languages and specialization in increasingly sought-after educational areas in the job market.\r\n\r\nEstablished in 2010, with headquarters inÂ Padua, Brescia, and Bologna,Â it is an institution affiliated with the university system byÂ Ministerial Decree of 12/03/2010.Â The educational offerings include aÂ three-year Bachelorâs Degree in Sciences of Language Mediation â Degree Class L-12 and a Masterâs Degree in Strategic Communication â Degree Class LM-94, as well as masterâs and advanced training courses for professionals.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSurvival Italian classes for international students\r\nSurvival Italian classes is an intensive program designed to teach foreign students attending a course at Ferrari Fashion School the basics of Italian language and culture, quickly and efficiently.\r\n\r\nThe importance of these courses lies in their ability to provide the basic linguistic tools necessary to handle everyday situations, thereby facilitating greater independence and confidence in a foreign context.\r\nWhy choose Survival Italian classes?\r\nTo reduce the language barrier and promote greater cultural and social integration. These courses utilize methodologies that make learning more enjoyable but also more effective and practical, as they encourage the active use of the language in real contexts, thus facilitating a rapid acquisition of essential communicative skills.\r\nCourse Details\r\nSurvival Italian classes (final level: A1)\r\n\r\nInstitution:Â The course offers the opportunity to reach levelÂ A1Â in theÂ ItalianÂ language. The course is offered byÂ CIELS Campus, a university that providesÂ BachelorâsÂ andÂ Masterâs DegreesÂ inÂ Linguistic MediationÂ andÂ Interpreting.\r\n\r\nWhen: The course can be repeated several times during the course of the year upon reaching the minimum number of students.\r\n\r\nDuration: 36 hours. The course is designed to provide in a relatively short time enough knowledge to ensure that Ferrari Fashion School students can have a minimum level of proficiency in Italian.\r\n\r\nCost per student:Â â¬300.00.\r\n\r\nMin. amount of students to activate the class:Â 10.\r\nEnglish course\r\n\r\nEnhance your language skills and achieve B2 level by participating in the intensive English course developed in collaboration with CIELS. This educational experience will guide you to success and enable you to acquire the competencies required for Bachelor of Arts.\r\n\r\nCourse details\r\n\r\n 	Institution: CIELSÂ offers Bachelor\'s and Masterâs Degrees in Linguistic Mediation and Interpreting.\r\n 	Course final level: B2\r\n 	Duration: 36 hours\r\n 	The first part (18 hours) will be asynchronous, the second one (18 hours) will be synchronous.\r\n 	When (second part): June and July, once a week.\r\n 	Cost per student: â¬300.00.\r\n 	Min. amount of students to activate the class: 10.\r\n 	Entry level required:Â B1\r\n\r\n\r\nREQUEST INFORMATION\r\nFill in the form and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\r\nWould you prefer to speak directly with our Orientation Team?\r\nClick here and book a personalised interview.', 'Student Service', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'services', '', '', '2025-01-23 10:14:17', '2025-01-23 09:14:17', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=2943', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(301, 3, '2019-12-09 10:18:27', '2019-12-09 09:18:27', '\r\nI Pattern Cutting - Shingo Sato\r\n\r\nPattern Cutting - Shingo Sato\r\nShort Course â Milano\r\nThe Japanese artist, Mr. Shingo Sato, creator of the âTR Pattern Cuttingâ technique, in collaboration with Ferrari Fashion School will hold 3 courses of 2-3 days each (TR Cutting Beginners, TR Cutting Advanced andÂ  Origami Workshop), at our School in Milan.\r\n\r\nDuring the course he will show his innovative technique for 3D pattern-making, which is creative and inductive for prototyping patterns, halfway from the draping and the classical pattern-making.\r\n\r\nThe students will be taught how to create new 3D patterns directly working on the mannequin, starting from ready-to-use bases. âTRâ stands for âTransformational Reconstructionâ, showing the process that the garment goes through when being created.\r\nCourse Details:\r\nLocation: Milano - Via Savona, 97\r\n\r\nClasses Time Table: dalle 9:00 alle 17:30\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDates\r\n\r\nFebruary: TR Pattern Cutting Beginners\r\n\r\nFebruary: TR Pattern Cutting Advanced\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFees:\r\n\r\nTR Cutting Beginners: â¬600\r\n\r\nTR Cutting Advanced: â¬600\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTRC Beginners + Advanced Package: â¬1.000,00\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\nAll the fees include Enrolment FebruaryÂ fee and VAT.\r\nThey also include teaching material, such as mannequins, sewing machines, stationery. Commodities is excluded. All participants will received a list of all the material to purchase for the course.\r\n\r\nTR CUTTING BEGINNERS\r\n\r\nFebruary\r\n\r\nTR CUTTING ADVANCED\r\n\r\nFebruary\r\n\r\nTR CUTTING BASE\r\n\r\n8-9-10 Febbraio\r\n\r\nTR CUTTING AVANZATO\r\n\r\n11-12-13 Febbraio 2020\r\n\r\nORIGAMI\r\n\r\n7-8 Ottobre\r\nASK FOR INFORMATION\r\nADMISSIONS AND ENROLMENT\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe courses are dedicated to who has at least 18 y.o., students or professionals in the fashion field, pattern-makers, tailors or simple enthusiasts who want to deepen and specialize in the TR Cutting technique and learn the secrets and design methodology of this particular technique, working together with a very talented and internationally known artist.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt is possible to enroll in only one course or more than one, if the applicant matches the requirements.\r\n\r\nThe number of seats in the class are limited. We kindly suggest to enrol in advance to book the seat in the classroom.\r\n\r\nThe course will start when the minimum number of students is reached.\r\n\r\nAt the end of the course a Certificate of Attendance will be issued.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTARGET\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Advanced Course is dedicated to those who have already completed the basic course and are willing to specialize in learning new advanced transformation techniques.\r\n\r\nOrigami Workshop instead illustrates the methodology of design, development and realization of garments and details with origami technique according to the TR Transformational Reconstruction technique used by the master Shingo Sato.\r\n\r\nAll participants must own basic knowledge and skills in sewing and autonomy in using the sewing machine.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEDUCATIONAL GOALS\r\nThe main purpose of the course is to learn the design techniques and development methods of this innovative 3D pattern-making technique to develop increasingly original and creative patterns, where construction, form and volumes play key-role.\r\nSTUDY PLAN\r\n\r\nBEGINNERS COURSE PROGRAM (3 DAYS):\r\nDay 1\r\n\r\nfrom 9.00am to 12.30pm - from 2.00pm to 5.30pm\r\n\r\nTechnical presentation, realization on the meta-base (sewing practice and eTR basic process) exercise on the skirt (volumetric integration) TR basic draping\r\n\r\nDay 2\r\n\r\nfrom 9.00am to 12.30pm - from 2.00pm to 5.30pm\r\n\r\nTechnical presentation, realization of TR draping twisted, band integration, origami pocket, Box integration, \"balloon technique\".\r\n\r\nDay 3\r\n\r\nfrom 9.00am to 12.30pm - from 2.00pm to 5.30pm\r\n\r\nTechnical presentation, realization of sleeve transformation, origami technique, multiple creations, TR Transformational Reconstruction techniques.\r\nSTUDY PLAN - ADVANCED COURSE (3 DAYS):\r\nDay 1\r\n\r\nfrom 9.00am to 12.30pm - from 2.00pm to 5.30pm\r\n\r\nPresentation and technical implementation, exercises âBOX Integrationâ, âAdvanced Vortex Tecniqueâ.\r\n\r\nDay 2\r\n\r\nfrom 9.00am to 12.30pm - from 2.00pm to 5.30pm\r\n\r\nPresentation and technical implementation of TR draping âTrompe l\'oeilâ Tecnique, Reticular Origami and seamed Tecnique\r\n\r\nDay 3\r\n\r\nfrom 9.00am to 12.30pm - from 2.00pm to 5.30pm\r\n\r\nTechnical presentation, multiple creations, TR Transformational Reconstruction techniques.\r\nASK FOR MORE INFORMATION\r\', 'Pattern Cutting - Shingo Sato', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pattern-cutting-shingo-sato', '', '', '2024-01-25 10:35:07', '2024-01-25 09:35:07', '', 2974, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=2947', 0, 'page', '', 0),
