(306, 3, '2019-12-17 09:37:40', '2019-12-17 08:37:40', '\r\nFashion Design\r\n\r\nFashion Design\r\nSummer Course - Milan\r\nPROVE YOUR TALENT AND DISCOVER ALL THE SECRETS OF THE ART OF TAILORING! MOVE YOUR FIRST STEPS IN THE WORLD OF\r\nFASHION AND LETâS BUILD YOUR PROFESSIONAL FUTURE TOGETHER BY WORKING IN A REAL STYLE-OFFICE!\r\n\r\nThe course is specifically about the techniques for rendering and drawing sketches, opening your mind to imagination and\r\ncreation of many different type of garments and accessories. The course will allow students learn, starting from the basis, the\r\nworking methodology and graphic planning of a fashion collection: from the study of the trends to drawing sketches, to the\r\ntechnical and graphic creation of a collection.\r\nAt the end, all participants will be given an Attendance Certificate.\r\nCourse details:\r\nLocation:Â Milan\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse duration: 40 hours\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬1464\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse duration: 80Â hours\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬2440\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse duration: 120Â hours\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬3294\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe cost includes texts and handouts, the registration fee and 22% VAT\r\nTARGET\r\nThe course is dedicated to beginners and those who start from zero.\r\nSTUDY PLAN\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Study of Anatomy\r\n 	Study of the Silhouettes\r\n 	Color Theory\r\n 	Color Matching\r\n 	Garnish Techniques\r\n 	Fashion Sketches\r\n 	Fashion Rendering Techniques\r\n 	Idea Creation\r\n 	Illustration\r\n 	Fashion Accessories\r\n 	Project-planning techniques\r\n 	Portfolio Collection (Capsule)\r\n 	Technical Sheet\r\n 	Methodology of Research\r\n\r\nASK FOR ', 'Fashion Design Course (Men or women)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'fashion-design-men-or-women', '', '', '2023-11-10 16:55:17', '2023-11-10 15:55:17', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=2997', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(307, 3, '2019-12-17 10:07:43', '2019-12-17 09:07:43', '\r\nIÂ CourseÂ  in Fashion Project ManagementÂ \r\n\r\nCourseÂ  in Fashion Project ManagementÂ \r\nSummer Course - Milan\r\nThe Fashion Project Management course aims to explain and analyze the features of the Italian fashion industry, the typical peculiarities of this system and the problems in creating a fashion product.\r\nDettagli del corso:\r\nLocation: Milan\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse duration:Â 40 hours\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬2684\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe cost includes texts and handouts, the registration fee and 22% VAT\r\nTARGET\r\nthe course is dedicated to academic professors in the field of Fashion, who want to refine their knowledge and keep up-to-date with the creative process and creation of fashion product.\r\nSTUDY PLAN\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Analysis of the Fashion System and related production chain and product communication with a focus on working methodology of the Italian Brands for the Made in Italy;\r\n 	Visits to Concept Stores;\r\n 	Methodology of Research: research and analysis of the trends, from research to creating a portfolio;\r\n 	History of the Made in Italy: visit through Milan (Armani Silos/Prada Foundation, etc.) or through Florence (Pitti Palace/Gallery of Costume, etc), previously agreed between the parts;\r\n 	Study of materials and commodities;\r\n 	How to manage and push forward a collection: from the study to the realization of a sample and related problems;\r\n 	Brand identity: study and planning of the personal collection portfolio and creative identity;\r\n 	Project review of the participant works, analysis and talk.\r\n\r\nASK FOR ', 'Fashion Project Management', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'fashion-project-management', '', '', '2020-01-20 12:14:21', '2020-01-20 11:14:21', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=3001', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(308, 3, '2019-12-17 10:58:26', '2019-12-17 09:58:26', '\r\nIÂ COURSE in PORTFOLIO COLLECTION\r\n\r\nCOURSE in PORTFOLIO COLLECTION\r\nSummer Course â Milan\r\nIl Corso di Portfolio CollectionÂ Â offre allo studente Â la capacitÃ  diÂ apprendere e analizzare le caratteristiche dellâindustria della Moda italiana e delle peculiaritÃ  tipiche di questo sistema.\r\nCourse details:\r\nLocation: Milan\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse duration: 40 hours\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬1464\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe cost includes texts and handouts, the registration fee and 22% VAT.\r\nTARGET\r\nThe summer course in Portfolio Collection is dedicated to all students from Fashion Institutes and High School (at least 18 years old) or colleges and universities with a minimum knowledge in the field of Fashion Design.\r\nSTUDY PLAN\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Analysis of the Fashion System and related production chain and product communication;\r\n 	Visits to Concept Stores;\r\n 	Methodology of Research: how to research, sources of inspirations for planning a collection, how to\r\nrecognize trends from above/below;\r\n 	Moodboard: how to create one starting from collage/magazines/pc, etc.;\r\n 	Fashion Collection: how to create a collection (with a given topic), how to choose colors and fabrics;\r\n 	Technical Design and Product development;\r\n 	Overview on the development system and prototyping of a sample sets: from pattern-making to unflawiof the garment (theory and practice);\r\n 	Brand identity: study and planning of the personal collection portfolio and creative identity;\r\n 	Project review of the participant works, analysis and talk.\r\n\r\nASK FOR ', 'Portfolio Collection', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'portfolio-collection', '', '', '2020-01-20 12:15:38', '2020-01-20 11:15:38', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=3006', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(309, 3, '2019-12-17 11:15:27', '2019-12-17 10:15:27', '\r\nIÂ COURSEÂ  IN PSYCHOLOGY AND RETAIL DESIGNÂ \r\n\r\nCOURSEÂ  IN PSYCHOLOGY AND RETAIL DESIGNÂ \r\nShort Course - Milan\r\nToday\'s stores are necessarily different from those of 10/15 years ago, just think of the enormity of the offer and the multiple distribution channels.\r\n\r\nOnline shopping has confirmed to be the definitive change in physical retail, it is no longer a simple display of products but fully participates in defining the identity of the Brand, constantly renewing itself to distinguish from competitors and leaving its mark on habitual and future consumers.\r\n\r\nShopping in a physical store has become a perceptive and relational experience, where brands define their uniqueness through multi-sensory involvement and the use of intangible components.\r\nHow to create a successful retail:\r\n&nbsp;\r\nKNOWLEDGE OF BRAND + VALUES\r\nREFERENCE TARGET +TECHNICAL DRAWING SKILLS\r\n\r\nCourse details:\r\nLocation: Milan\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDates:Â 17thÂ  - 18thÂ  July 2019\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDuration:Â 2 days\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬500\r\n\r\n(â¬100 discount reserved for the first 10 subscribers)The cost includes texts and handouts, the registration fee and 22% VATWe will talk about:\r\n\r\nBrand Identity / Emotions and Buying Behavior / Window Dressing / Equipment Layout / Commodity Layout / Use of Color / Use of Lighting\r\nTARGET\r\nThe course is dedicated to people over 18, students from Fashion and Design schools or simply enthusiasts who want to deeply study issues related to the world of psychology in the field of retail design. A basic culture in fashion is required.\r\nTRAINING GOALS\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Sharpen individual sensitivity in identifying Brand Identity strategies\r\n 	Knowledge of techniques for the design of commercial spaces\r\n\r\n\r\nSTUDY PROGRAMS\r\nFIRST DAY\r\n\r\n9:30 - 12:30\r\n\r\nTheory\r\n\r\n14:00 - 14:45\r\n\r\nLaboratory and Design: Design and plan your future retail\r\n\r\n2.45pm - 4.00pm\r\n\r\nAnalysis and review of projects\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSECOND DAY\r\n\r\n10.00 - 12:30\r\n\r\nTheory\r\n\r\n13:30 - 16:00\r\n\r\nLaboratory and practical activity: The highly professional approach and the skills acquired during the training are made possible thanks to direct contact and research at the most important showrooms and luxury stores in Milan, the international capital of fashion. Through the study of the Fashion System and of the most important international brands, it will be possible to carry out research and analysis of various types of retail and visual concepts, where participants can experience a multisensory experience from which they can draw new ideas.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nASK FOR ', 'Psychology and Retail Design', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'psychology-and-retail-design', '', '', '2020-01-20 13:44:47', '2020-01-20 12:44:47', '', 2970, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=3009', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(310, 3, '2019-12-17 12:02:54', '2019-12-17 11:02:54', '\r\nI Course in Stylist &amp; Visual Merchandiser\r\n\r\nCourse in Stylist &amp; Visual Merchandiser\r\nSummer Course - Milan\r\nThe Stylist &amp; Visual Merchandiser Course aims to learn and analyze the strategies of Visual Merchandising, Styling and image consultancy of Italian fashion towards different types of customers and contexts.\r\nCourse details Â :\r\nLocation: Milan\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCourse duration: 40 hours\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬1464\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe cost includes texts and handouts, the registration fee and 22% VAT\r\nTARGET\r\nThe Stylist &amp; Visual Merchandiser Course is dedicated to:\r\n\r\n 	Fashion students from high school institutes (minimum 18 years) or academies and universities with a minimum knowledge of Fashion Design.\r\n 	Fashion sector professionals, such as journalists, designers, retailers and stylists, who already work in the sector, but with a preparation that is not necessarily adequate and who, therefore, want to deepen their knowledge in the field of Fashion Styling and Visual Merchandising.\r\n\r\n\r\nStudy Plan:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Fashion Styling: what is and how it works;\r\n 	Concept Identity and Clients system;\r\n 	Fashion Editorials and Fashion Magazine;\r\n 	Creation and strategy in the Fashion Story Telling;\r\n 	Brand Identity and Fashion Trends analysis;\r\n 	Cool Hunting and Fashion Search;\r\n 	Fashion Business and Worldwide customers;\r\n 	The wardrobe and its rules;\r\n 	Psychology of the Fashion Trade &amp; Visual system;\r\n 	On-site Practice with visits to Concept stores;\r\n 	Project review of the participant works, analysis and talk.\r\n\r\n\r\nASK FOR ', 'Stylist & Visual Merchandiser', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'stylist-visual-merchandiser', '', '', '2020-01-20 12:15:52', '2020-01-20 11:15:52', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=3014', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(311, 3, '2019-12-17 12:09:13', '2019-12-17 11:09:13', '\r\nIÂ T-Shirt Design\r\n\r\nCOURSE in T-SHIRT DESIGN\r\nShort Course - Milan\r\nTest your talent and design your T-shirt collection! Use your creativity and learn to design graphics and prints, designs and applications for unique and original T-shirts!\r\n\r\nThe course allows you to create many creative ideas and create your own customized T-shirt!\r\nTARGET\r\nThe course is dedicated to young students or enthusiasts over 16 y.o. who want to test their creativity and take their first steps in the fields of design, graphics and fashion.\r\nDettagli del corso:\r\nLocation: Milan\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDates:Â \r\n\r\nFrom July 1stÂ  to 5thÂ  2019\r\n\r\nFrom July 8thÂ  to 12thÂ  2019\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDuration: 1 Week\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCost of the course: â¬ 500\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe cost includes texts and handouts, the registration fee and 22% VAT.\r\nHISTORY OF THE T-SHIRT\r\nThe t-shirt or simply tee is a piece of clothing made of fabric, without buttons and without collar, which covers the bust of the wearer.\r\n\r\nIt can be made with long sleeves or short sleeves, in natural fabrics like cotton, or in synthetic fibers. There are plain-colored or multi-colored fancy t-shirts.\r\n\r\nBorn at the end of the 19th century as a work clothes for sailors and later became part of the uniform of American soldiers in the 1940s, during the 1900s it became one of the most versatile garments used for generations, dressing people of all ages , social class and nation.\r\n\r\nFamous actors such as James Dean or Marlon Brando wore the typical white short-sleeved T-shirt over a pair of jeans on the big screen: from that moment on, the t-shirt definitely entered contemporary fashion.\r\n\r\nIt was in the eighties that the t-shirt established itself as a creative garment and a communicative vehicle through ornamental friezes and writings: the message transmitted through the t-shirts assumed the most disparate and ironic forms and meanings (the first smile appeared on some t-shirt), advertising, political or geographical.\r\n\r\nEven today, the T-shirt is a piece of clothing considered the basis of must-haves and the most versatile garment in the wardrobe of each of us.\r\nSTUDY PLAN\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Basics of Design\r\n 	Bases of anatomy\r\n 	History of the T-Shirt: Models and variants\r\n 	Illustration techniques\r\n 	Study of the T-Shirt: technical drawing\r\n 	Color Theory\r\n 	Staining techniques\r\n 	Computer Graphics: Photoshop 1-Base Level\r\n 	Basic Elements of Textile Design: Graphics and Printing\r\n 	Study of materials\r\n 	Moodboard Design\r\n 	Portfolio Collection (Capsules)\r\n 	Prototype realization of 1 T-Shirt chosen by the student\r\n\r\nASK FOR ', 'T-Shirt Design', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 't-shirt-design', '', '', '2020-01-20 12:37:46', '2020-01-20 11:37:46', '', 2970, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=3018', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(312, 3, '2019-12-17 14:16:58', '2019-12-17 13:16:58', '\r\nIÂ CAD 2D / 3D\r\n\r\nWITH ASSYST AND FERRARI FASHION SCHOOL THE NEW PROFESSION OF THE FUTURE IS BORN! BECOME 3D ARTIST WITH THE NEW VIDYA ASSYST TECHNOLOGY!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFerrari Fashion School is always attentive to new emerging professional figures in the fashion field. For this reason we have chosen ASSYST, one of the most important and cutting-edge companies in terms of technology, in terms of research and development of new CAD / CAM 2D and 3D CAD software for fashion. This new partnership allows us to offer our students up-to-date tools and cutting-edge technologies, as well as interesting career opportunities and professional growth, offering them specialization courses that see, in addition to the 2D Cad model also the birth of a new professional figure: that of 3D ARTIST.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMany prestigious brands and leading luxury fashion companies such as Versace, Benetton, Liu Jo, Max Mara, Hugo Boss, Diesel, Yamamay and many others have chosen Assyst\'s innovative fashion technologies to design and develop their collections.\r\nÂ WATCH THE VIDEOS TO DISCOVER WHAT THIS IS!\r\n\r\nFIND OUT MORE ABOUT THE STUDY PROGRAMS AND THE DETAILS OF THE COURSES\r\nBOOK A CUSTOM OPEN ', 'Cad Pattern-Making', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cad-courses', '', '', '2020-01-31 12:25:23', '2020-01-31 11:25:23', '', 2970, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=3021', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(313, 3, '2019-12-17 14:38:48', '2019-12-17 13:38:48', '\r\nMaster of Arts\r\nFashion Design\r\nand Creative Direction\r\n\r\nCourse Details\r\nLocation: Milan Fashion Business District\r\n\r\nDuration: 16 months\r\n\r\nStart: January 2026\r\n\r\nCredits: 180 UK credits - 90 ECTS\r\n\r\nClasses: max 10 students\r\n\r\nLanguage: English\r\n\r\nAward Title: Master of Arts in Fashion Design and Creative Direction with/without Advanced Practice\r\n\r\nEducational Partner: Teesside University\r\nThe programme emphasizes a forward-thinking and experimental approach to fashion, encouraging students to develop their own unique aesthetic language. It fosters a critical mindset, where fashion is seen as a medium to communicate ideas and explore complex themes, such as identity, cultural and social issues. Students are encouraged to question conventions and experiment with new forms, materials, and techniques with a focus on sustainability and circular practices.\r\nDistinctive features include creative directors and emerging brandsâ founders as lecturers and guest speakers, textile lab practice, extensive time in the fashion lab, external visits to textile companies, a study trip abroad, and advanced practice (internship / research project / design competitions).\r\n\r\nThis course is validated by Teesside University, which will award the degree upon successful completion of the program.INFO REQUEST\r\nMain topics\r\n\r\nResearch and\r\nDevelopment\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Creative Research\r\n 	Critical Thinking\r\n 	Design Iteration\r\n\r\n\r\nMaterials\r\nand Tailoring\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Circularity and Upcyling\r\n 	Textile Innovation and Manipulation\r\n 	Craftsmanship and Tailoring\r\n\r\n\r\nFashion\r\nMaking\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Sustainability and Eco Design\r\n 	Collection Development\r\n 	Garment Construction\r\n\r\n\r\nCreative\r\nDirection\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Personal Manifesto\r\n 	Aesthetics and Visual Language\r\n 	Brand Image\r\n\r\n\r\nFashion immersion\r\nThe course offers students a unique opportunity to expand their horizons and delve into the fashion capital of the world, Milan, which provides a dynamic ecosystem that guarantees students a variety of opportunities to explore and engage with the international fashion scene through events, trade fairs, visits to museums and cultural initiatives related to the world of Fashion, Design and Art. Milan Fashion Week, Fuorisalone, Design week, and Photography Exhibitions are some of the must-attend events for stimulating experiences that students can enjoy while studying their Masterâs.Personalized Career Advisory sessions are embedded into the programme.\r\nLecturers and Guest speakers include: Alice Firman (Course Leader), Luciano Bandi, Gianluca Cantaro, Leone Scordo, Paulo Melim Andersson, Enea Burattoni, Flora Rabitti, Marcello Pipitone, Federico Alpi, Nicola Benedettini.INFO REQUEST\r\nTarget audience\r\nThe course is designed for fashion designers and creative individuals eager to advance their knowledge and skillset, experiment, focus on their individual development, and refine their creative identity. Aimed at aspiring designers and ambitious fashion professionals, the programme provides practical training, hands-on learning, global perspectives and industry connections to lead the future of fashion pushing for sustainability and ethical practices.\r\nEducational aim\r\nThe course aims to elevate quality and excellence in the field of design and creative direction in the fashion sector. Through a balanced approach between practical training and theoretical insights, the program is designed to provide students with advanced skills in the field of fashion design, enabling them to emerge as highly qualified professionals. Additionally, the course aims to teach the art of creating unique, distinctive, and cutting-edge designs, promoting innovation and sustainability in the design process. Designing captivating concepts and producing garments are integral parts of the course, aimed at translating students\' artistic ideas into tangible pieces combined with projects of strong visual impact. Finally, the course provides a deep understanding of the production cycle, refining the necessary skills to lead the creative team and develop collections that respect the brand\'s historical identity while ensuring an innovative and competitive approach in the market.\r\nAdmission requirements\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Bachelor\'s degree - first-level bachelor\'s degree and/or work experience in Fashion, Design, or Business areas.\r\n 	Students whose native language is not English must demonstrate language proficiency equivalent to an IELTS score of at least 6.0 - students lacking language skills will be supported before the start of the course.\r\n 	Additionally, a motivational letter, a portfolio (if available), and participation in an admission interview are required.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Bachelor\'s degree - first-level bachelor\'s degree and/or work experience in Fashion, Design, or Business areas.\r\n 	Official translation of the academic title and transcripts (if not already in Italian or English).\r\n 	Students whose native language is not English must demonstrate language proficiency equivalent to an IELTS score of at least 6.0 - students lacking language skills will be supported before the start of the course.\r\n 	Residence permit/permit application, to be submitted to the orientation office within 8 working days of arrival in Italy.\r\n 	Additionally, a motivational letter, a portfolio (if available), and participation in an admission interview are required.\r\n\r\nFor additional and detailed information regarding entry requirements based on your country of origin, we invite youÂ to visit the Teesside University website.\r\n\r\n\r\nDon\'t meet the requirements? Discover the preparatory course in Fashion and Luxury Graduate Programme.\r\n\r\nThe Master in Fashion Design and Creative Direction can open doors to multiple career prospects, including:The creator of the brand\'s vision and creative identity in terms of design and communication.The coordinator of the entire design process for specific collections of the brand.Designer in charge of specific lines (MW, WW, knitwear, jersey, denim, etc.).\r\nResearcher of new and innovative materials (fabrics, trims).\r\nEco fashion designer with a focus on environmental and social impact evaluation.Entrepreneur of a new fashion brand.\r\nREQUEST INFORMATION\r\nFill in the form and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\r\nWould you prefer to speak directly with our Orientation Team?\r\nClick here and book a personalised interview.\r\', 'MA Fashion Design and Creative Direction', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'womenswear-design-portfolio', '', '', '2025-01-08 19:18:05', '2025-01-08 18:18:05', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=3029', 0, 'page', '', 0),
