(315, 3, '2020-01-21 11:16:20', '2020-01-21 10:16:20', '\r\nPartners\r\nThe strong international orientation and the constant updating of educational programs in line with corporate standards make Ferrari Fashion School proactive in weaving a network of collaborations with prominent national and international companies, universities, and institutional partners such as: Fashion Training System Platform, Confindustria Moda, Milan Fashion Week, Milan Furniture Fair, National Chamber of Fashion in Milan, Lombardy Region, and Municipality of Milan, Milan Triennale, Pitti Immagine, American Institute of Applied Sciences in Switzerland, Dar Al-Hekma University, Teesside University.\r\nEducational Partnership\r\n\r\nInstitutional Partners\r\n\r\nCollaborations\r\nFerrari Fashion School is active in promoting young talents and offers numerous opportunities to its students, such as participation in contests, events, exhibitions, and exclusive fashion shows that take place during the most important national and international events. In order to expand relavant opportunities of personal and professional growth, the Academy, its students and alumni have collaborated (internship/ stage / academic projects / technical sponsorships) with renowned companies, including:ACAPULCO, ANTONIOLI, ARMANI, ARCHETIPO, BASICNET (KWAY, SUPERGA, KAPPA), BERTO TESSUTI, BONAVERI, CAP74024 MAGAZINE, DAVINES, DOLCE&amp;GABBANA, GABRIELE COLANGELO, GOLDEN GOOSE, ISAIA, JIL SANDER, KERING INNOVATION MATERIAL LAB, LAMPO, LIMONTA, LORO PIANA, MANTECO, MILANO UNICA, MISSONI, MUSEO POLDI PEZZOLI, MVP WARDROBE, NEOUS, ONIVERSE GROUP (CALZEDONIA, INTIMISSIMI, FALCONERI, ATELIER EMÃ), REDA, SARTORIA A. CARACENI, TOM FORD, TRIENNALE DI MILANO, VALENTINO, VERSACE, VITALE BARBERIS CANONICO.', 'Partners', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'partners', '', '', '2024-10-30 14:39:26', '2024-10-30 13:39:26', '', 0, 'https://www.ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=2993', 0, 'page', '', 0),
