(349, 1, '2022-07-05 09:37:40', '2022-07-05 07:37:40', '\r\n3 Year Course\r\nFashion Design\r\n\r\nCourse Details\r\nLocation: Milan\r\n\r\nDuration: 3 academic years\r\n\r\nStart: October 2025\r\n\r\nCredits: 180 CF\r\n\r\nClass size: max 15 students\r\n\r\nLanguage: Italian\r\nBecome a professional in the fashion design sector capable of conceptualizing and creating a fashion collection, clothing, and accessories that reflect and enhance your artistic and aesthetic sensitivity.\r\nThe course is designed for those who wish to express their creativity, bring new trends to life in response to consumer demand, and produce a finished product from initial design. Meet professors with strong academic and professional experience gained in the most important fashion houses, capable of imparting knowledge and research methodologies, analysis, and design in line with current industry standards to maximize your creative and design potential.INFO REQUEST\r\nMain topics\r\n\r\nFashion\r\nFundamentals\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Fashion Design\r\n 	Fashion Trend Analysis\r\n 	Fashion Drawing and Illustration\r\n\r\n\r\nPresentation\r\nand Communication\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Portfolio Production\r\n 	Visual Communication\r\n 	Contemporary Fashion\r\n\r\n\r\nCreative\r\nDevelopment\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Fashion Collection\r\n 	Fashion Show and Events\r\n 	Creative Laboratory\r\n\r\n\r\nMaterials\r\nand Techniques\r\n\r\n\r\n 	Textile Innovation\r\n 	PatternmakingÂ \r\n 	Tailoring\r\n\r\n\r\nDiscover the Fashion Designer profession\r\nThe Fashion Designer is a versatile professional with fundamental skills to design and create a fashion collection, including garments or accessories. They play a leading role within their team, taking on the responsibility of coordinating and supervising every phase of the process, from the initial design phase to the realization of the finished product. Thanks to their innate creativity and aesthetic sensitivity, the Fashion Designer is not only able to predict trends but also to create new ones, in order to meet the ever-changing needs of a continuously evolving market.INFO REQUEST\r\nTarget audience\r\nThe course is designed for all students passionate about fashion and creativity, eager to transform their passion into a successful career. Aimed at aspiring designers, students from any high school background, fashion enthusiasts with creative inclinations, the course aims to provide practical skills and in-depth knowledge.\r\nEducational aim\r\nThe course aims to ensure adequate mastery of artistic methods and techniques, as well as the acquisition of specific disciplinary and professional skills, to provide students with design and expressive knowledge and methodologies in the use of representation tools and artistic practices, with particular attention to fashion. The fundamental objectives in the education of graduates in Fashion Design concern the knowledge and understanding of the dynamics of the fashion system, in Italy and globally, as well as the acquisition of methodological and technical-instrumental skills necessary for the design of products in the fashion sector supply chain, including textile products, clothing, and accessories.\r\nAdmission requirements\r\n\r\n\r\n 	High school diploma or another degree obtained abroad confirming 12 years of schooling.\r\n 	Official translation of the diploma and transcripts (if not already in Italian or English).\r\n 	Passing the admission tests.\r\n 	Motivational letter.\r\n\r\nStudents holding a five-year IPSIA diploma with a fashion specialization or artistic maturity are exempt from admission tests and have direct access to the course*.\r\n\r\n\r\n 	High school diploma or another degree obtained abroad confirming 12 years of schooling, recognized through a \"Dichiarazione di Valore (DV)\".\r\n 	Official translation of the diploma and transcripts (if not already in Italian or English).\r\n 	Italian language certification B2 - students without a language certification will be supported before the start of the course to acquire the required certification.\r\n 	Passing the admission tests.\r\n 	Residence permit/application for a residence permit, to be submitted to the orientation office within 8 working days of arrival in Italy.\r\n 	Motivational letter.\r\n\r\nThe course in Design della moda can open doors to multiple career opportunities including:You will have the opportunity to express your creativity through the design and creation of fashionable clothing, footwear, and accessories. You will collaborate with dynamic teams to develop unique pieces that reflect current market trends, contributing to the success of the brand\'s product line.You will have the opportunity to establish your own brand, design your personal collections or for third parties, and develop its commercial identity in the fashion sector.You will be the main creator of the creative vision and artistic identity of the company. You will lead the creative process, collaborating with designers, photographers, and marketers to ensure consistency and innovation in projects.You will have the opportunity to shape the future of a brand\'s products, combining form, function, and aesthetics. You will work closely with multidisciplinary teams, including engineers and marketing managers, to create products that stand out for their quality and innovative design.You will oversee the entire design process within the company. You will manage design teams, implement creative strategies, and supervise the overall visual aesthetics of the brand to maintain a high standard of design in all company products.You will analyze emerging trends in society, focusing on lifestyles, fashion, and popular culture. You will provide valuable insights to business decisions, helping to anticipate future market directions and remain competitive in the industry.\r\nREQUEST INFORMATION\r\nFill in the form and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\r\nWould you prefer to speak directly with our Orientation Team?\r\nClick here and book a personalised interview.\r\', 'Fashion Design', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'fashion-design', '', '', '2024-11-13 16:25:48', '2024-11-13 15:25:48', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=5575', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(350, 1, '2022-07-26 11:42:03', '2022-07-26 09:42:03', '\r\nCosa fa il Sarto?\r\nIl Sarto/a puÃ² ricoprire diversi ruoli allâinterno del ciclo di produzione di una collezione, a seconda che si occupi di prototipia, campionatura, confezione ecc..\r\nNel mondo della moda e nellâindustria tessile il Sarto/a Ã¨ una delle figure professionali piÃ¹ importanti e ricercate proprio per la sua capacitÃ  di concretizzare le idee dello stilista attraverso la sua capacitÃ  interpretativa, la grande manualitÃ , lâestrema precisione e lâaltissima competenza tecnica riguardo a forme, tessuti e materiali (e loro relative lavorazioni), da renderla una figura centrale e indispensabile allâinterno della filiera Moda.\r\nSi puÃ² definire un Artigiano del Lusso e puÃ² ricoprire diversi ruoli a seconda che si occupi di realizzare capi di Alta Moda su misura (Sarta/o PremiÃ¨re), dei prototipi (Sarta/o Prototipista) piuttosto che dei campionari (Sarta/o Campionarista), del taglio (Tagliatore) oppure di confezioni a livello industriale (Confezionista chiamato anche sarto industriale); si occupa della confezione di capi dâabbigliamento, curandone i particolari e rendendoli riconoscibili.\r\n\r\nIl Sarto/a Prototipista Ã¨ la figura professionale che si occupa di realizzare uno o piÃ¹ prototipi, ovvero un capo campione che viene tagliato e cucito a mano dalla sarta/o realizzando quello che il modellista ha progettato, per fare questo servono grande competenza e pazienza. Il risultato finale non Ã¨ un capo di prova, come una tela, ma un modello che ha le stesse caratteristiche di quello che verrÃ  prodotto se il designer ed il modellista approveranno il capo.\r\nTra le competenze acquisite nel corso di Sartoria Triennale troviamo anche quella del Campionarista, che rappresenta una figura di riferimento per molti processi di lavorazione e agisce da mediazione tra i vari cicli di lavorazione che contribuiscono alla messa a punto del prodotto ottimale.\r\nIl Confezionista infine gestisce il ciclo produttivo, interagisce con tutte le figure coinvolte nel processo industriale e possiede una buona manualitÃ  di tipo sartoriale. Il lavoro puÃ² essere eseguito utilizzando diverse tecniche.SCOPRI IL CORSO DI ALTA SARTORIA', 'Cosa fa il Sarto?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cosa-fa-il-sarto', '', '', '2023-09-12 16:12:49', '2023-09-12 14:12:49', '', 3903, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=6179', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(351, 1, '2022-07-26 11:54:47', '2022-07-26 09:54:47', 'La figura del Modellista Ã¨ molto ricercata in tutte le aziende che si occupano della produzione di abbigliamento.\r\n\r\nÃ una figura professionale con unâelevata preparazione tecnica nella progettazione di cartamodelli e prototipi di tutti i capi che compongono il guardaroba.\r\n\r\nIl Modellista concretizza le idee dello stilista trasformando i suoi schizzi in disegni tecnici in scala reale, per progettare e realizzare i vari pezzi necessari a comporre il capo. Deve rispettare le proporzioni del figurino e progettare il modello prima su carta, poi su tela di prova, creando il prototipo per la realizzazione del campionario.\r\n\r\nBuona manualitÃ  nel disegno tecnico, capacitÃ  di sviluppo, grande precisione e attenzione ai dettagli sono prerogative indispensabili per svolgere il suo lavoro.\r\n\r\nIn caso di produzioni di tipo sartoriale, realizza manualmente il cartamodello cosÃ¬ come tutte le fasi di sviluppo fino alla realizzazione del prototipo.\r\nNel caso di produzioni industriali, il Modellista puÃ² progettare i cartamodelli utilizzando programmi e software CAD 2D e 3D specifici per la Moda. In questâultimo caso il Modellista deve necessariamente saper progettare prima manualmente per poi imparare ad utilizzare i programmi CAD attraverso una formazione specialistica.SCOPRI IL CORSO DI MODELLISTA', 'Cosa fa il Modellista?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cosa-fa-il-modellista', '', '', '2023-09-12 16:14:20', '2023-09-12 14:14:20', '', 3903, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=6181', 0, 'page', '', 0);
