(410, 9, '2024-01-23 12:15:25', '2024-01-23 11:15:25', '\r\nSummer Course\r\nMilano ModaLab\r\n\r\nCourse Details\r\nLocation: Ferrari Fashion School â Via Savona 97 / Via Pestalozzi 4, Milano\r\n\r\nDates of the programmes:\r\n\r\n 	16 June â 26 June 2025\r\n 	30 June â 10 July 2025\r\n 	14 July â 24 July 2025\r\n\r\nDuration: 54 hours - 2 weeks\r\n\r\nMode: in presence\r\n\r\nLanguage: English B1/B2\r\n\r\nFinal Award: Certificate of Attendance by Ferrari Fashion School\r\n\r\nFee: 1,390.00 â¬\r\nMilano ModaLab is a summer camp aimed at young international and Italian students who want to live a unique experience in Milano and explore different disciplines: drawing, design, styling, and communication in one of the most prestigious Fashion Schools in Italy, whilst enriching their education and curriculum.\r\nMilano ModaLab is an intensive two-week programme designed for fashion enthusiasts and aspiring designers and creatives. Hosted in Milan, the global fashion capital, this course offers a unique blend of hands-on workshops, expert-led lectures, and exclusive visits to renowned fashion houses and ateliers.\r\n\r\nParticipants explore key aspects of the fashion industry, including trend forecasting, how the fashion system works, design &amp; garment construction, styling &amp; photography, fashion comunication. With guidance from fashion professionals, students gain insights into the latest trends, sustainable practices, and the creative processes that drive the world of contemporary fashion.\r\n\r\nThroughout the programme, participants work on different projects, culminating in a presentation where they can showcase their portfolio. Milano Moda Lab is perfect for those looking to enhance their skills and get inspired by the vibrant culture and lifestyle of Milanese fashion.INFO REQUEST\r\nSummer School focus\r\nExternal visits to museums, fashion foundations, showrooms, and ateliers are an integral part of the program and included in the fee.\r\nFashion System\r\nThis module introduces you to the world of fashion and its dynamics. You will learn how the fashion industry is structured, what a fashion week entails, and how to analyze a fashion show to forecast upcoming market trends.\r\nDesign\r\nThe module covers basic principles of fashion design, including how to conduct iconographic research, create a moodboard, and visualize new ideas through drawing and collage. You will also learn how to source materials and fabrics, as well as how to design garments using upcycling techniques.\r\nFashion Communication\r\nThis module introduces you to the methods and techniques of fashion journalism, social media, and communication, from both brand and magazine (online/print) perspectives.\r\nFashion Styling and Photography\r\nYou will learn how to create an editorial / commercial adv, to organize a photoshoot, selecting the right pieces, and to create a captivating visual story, with access to the Schoolâs Photo Studio.\r\nDate of Sessions\r\nSummer 2025\r\n\r\n\r\n 	16 June to 26 June 2025\r\n 	30 June to 10 July 2025\r\n 	14 July to 24 July 2025.\r\n\r\nAll sessions will be based on the same programme.\r\nFees\r\nFee: 1,390.00 â¬\r\n\r\nDiscounts:\r\n\r\n 	Very early bird by 28 February 2025 -15%;\r\n 	Early bird by 30 April 2025 -10%\r\n\r\nCourse package/groups/family: please contact admission@ferrarifashionschool.com\r\n\r\nIf the student, after the completion of the summer programme, enrolls in a BA, MA or Masterâs programme at Ferrari Fashion School, a 10% reduction will be applied to the annual tuition fee for the first year.\r\nAdmission requirements\r\n\r\n\r\n 	High school diploma or another degree obtained abroad confirming 12 years of schooling.\r\n 	Official translation of the diploma and transcripts (if not already in Italian or English).\r\n 	Passing the admission tests.\r\n 	Motivational letter.\r\n\r\nStudents holding a five-year IPSIA diploma with a fashion specialization or artistic maturity are exempt from admission tests and have direct access to the course*.\r\n\r\n\r\n 	High school diploma or another degree obtained abroad confirming 12 years of schooling, recognized through a \"Dichiarazione di Valore (DV)\".\r\n 	Official translation of the diploma and transcripts (if not already in Italian or English).\r\n 	Italian language certification B2 - students without a language certification will be supported before the start of the course to acquire the required certification.\r\n 	Passing the admission tests.\r\n 	Residence permit/application for a residence permit, to be submitted to the orientation office within 8 working days of arrival in Italy.\r\n 	Motivational letter.\r\n\r\nThe course in Design della moda can open doors to multiple career opportunities including:You will have the opportunity to express your creativity through the design and creation of fashionable clothing, footwear, and accessories. You will collaborate with dynamic teams to develop unique pieces that reflect current market trends, contributing to the success of the brand\'s product line.You will have the opportunity to establish your own brand, design your personal collections or for third parties, and develop its commercial identity in the fashion sector.You will be the main creator of the creative vision and artistic identity of the company. You will lead the creative process, collaborating with designers, photographers, and marketers to ensure consistency and innovation in projects.You will have the opportunity to shape the future of a brand\'s products, combining form, function, and aesthetics. You will work closely with multidisciplinary teams, including engineers and marketing managers, to create products that stand out for their quality and innovative design.You will oversee the entire design process within the company. You will manage design teams, implement creative strategies, and supervise the overall visual aesthetics of the brand to maintain a high standard of design in all company products.You will analyze emerging trends in society, focusing on lifestyles, fashion, and popular culture. You will provide valuable insights to business decisions, helping to anticipate future market directions and remain competitive in the industry.\r\nREQUEST INFORMATION\r\nFill in the form and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\r\nWould you prefer to speak directly with our Orientation Team?\r\nClick here and book a personalised interview.\r\', 'Milano ModaLab', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'milano-modalab', '', '', '2024-10-25 16:56:24', '2024-10-25 14:56:24', '', 0, 'https://ferrarifashionschool.it/?page_id=9470', 0, 'page', '', 0),
